properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Patchy frost is expected tonight. Clearing skies and a cool airmass will cause temperatures to dip to near or slightly below zero tonight causing patchy frost. Locations that remain cloudy will likely stay above the freezing mark. Frost advisories are issued from the Saturday of the Victoria Day weekend until September 30 when required. ### Frost advisories are issued when temperatures are expected to reach the freezing mark during the growing season, leading to potential damage and destruction to plants and crops. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ABstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ABStorm.

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A ridge of high pressure over the northern Prairies continues to circulate cool northeasterly winds across much of the Prairies. Temperatures are expected to drop to near or below the freezing mark tonight especially over western Manitoba. Extreme southern areas of the province will have a bit more cloud and slightly stronger winds that will aid in keeping temperatures from falling below freezing. Frost advisories are issued from the Saturday of the Victoria Day weekend to September 30 when required. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to MBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #MBStorm.

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A ridge of high pressure over the northern Prairies continues to circulate a cool northeasterly flow to much of Saskatchewan. This cool airmass will lead to fairly widespread frost tonight with temperatures expected to dip to near or slightly below the freezing mark. Cloud cover over the southeastern portion of the province should aid in keeping temperatures above the freezing mark in those areas tonight. However patchy frost may be possible there as well if skies clear significantly. Frost advisories are issued from the Saturday of the Victoria Day weekend until September 30 when required. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Summary:
Description: Periods of rain will continue until late Monday with rainfall amounts of 20 to 40 mm possible. Thunderstorms may accompany the rain today. Locally higher rainfall amounts are possible in areas that receive thunderstorms. Localized flooding is possible. For information concerning flooding, please consult your local Conservation Authority or Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry District Office. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
